All right, well, let's continue to worship our God.

00:05.685 --> 00:06.505
Let's study his word.

00:06.525 --> 00:09.409
Go ahead and turn in your Bible, if you would, to Acts chapter 20.

00:14.274 --> 00:22.343
Acts chapter 20, and we're gonna break this up into two weeks, tackling this text from verse 17 through verse 35.

00:22.363 --> 00:24.145
I'll read it in just a minute.

00:24.905 --> 00:25.806
Just a heads up.

00:25.887 --> 00:32.754
So first, I was planning on preaching this entire passage in one message and had six points, and then,

00:33.026 --> 00:35.409
realize I'm not gonna be able to get to all six of those points.

00:35.469 --> 00:39.553
And so divided it into a two part sort of mini series in Acts chapter 20.

00:40.254 --> 00:44.939
And then I realized after developing the notes that you're looking at that we're not even gonna get to that.

00:45.160 --> 00:48.884
So the third point is not going to happen this morning.

00:49.204 --> 00:51.066
The first and second points are gonna happen.

00:51.667 --> 00:56.352
And so I can already sense the anxiety of those who get obsessive about filling in all the blanks.

00:57.033 --> 00:57.834
And I know you're out.

00:57.854 --> 00:58.715
I know who you are.

00:59.336 --> 01:01.298
I tend to hear from you from time to time.

01:01.666 --> 01:04.329
And so some of you worry, stress about this.

01:04.369 --> 01:05.650
We've got a website.

01:06.130 --> 01:08.933
And on the website, no blank is left behind.

01:08.973 --> 01:09.554
It's all there.

01:09.614 --> 01:10.435
You can find it.

01:10.495 --> 01:15.840
You can sense and get a feel for where the sermon is even going first thing on Sunday morning.

01:15.860 --> 01:19.644
So some of you will be dialing that in even now so you can make sure you have the third blank.

01:20.024 --> 01:24.168
And so I'm just going to punt that third point in the next week and we'll tackle it there.

01:25.409 --> 01:30.034
All right, so this is just some background, some context before we read the text.

01:30.178 --> 01:36.323
The first time in the book of Acts, the only time in the book of Acts where Paul is addressing an entirely Christian audience.

01:36.343 --> 01:38.645
This is a rather narrow audience.

01:38.685 --> 01:41.348
So Paul has summoned the Ephesian elders.

01:41.388 --> 01:43.369
He has worked in Ephesus for three years.

01:43.870 --> 01:44.851
Now he's in my lead us.

01:44.891 --> 01:48.074
He's been traveling around and he summons the Ephesian elders.

01:48.574 --> 01:51.637
And so this is a unique context into which he's speaking.

01:51.677 --> 01:57.181
It's a different kind of speech than the ones we've heard in earlier parts of Acts where we've heard lots of evangelistic sermons.

01:57.662 --> 02:00.164
We've heard legal defenses before Sanhedrons

02:00.144 --> 02:00.645
counsel.

02:00.685 --> 02:06.151
We'll get five more legal defenses in chapters 22 through 26, but this is different.

02:06.892 --> 02:10.797
And so here at the beginning of chapter 20, Paul is summoning the elders to my leaders.

02:10.837 --> 02:18.846
He's not just stationed there or sitting there in renting space in the hall of Tyrannus and teaching day after day after day in Ephesus.

02:18.906 --> 02:19.727
Now he's on the move.

02:19.747 --> 02:21.970
He's traveling through various regions as if he had

02:22.274 --> 02:24.056
prior to the third missionary journey.

02:24.596 --> 02:27.438
And now he's in my lead us and he's calling the elders to himself.

02:27.479 --> 02:37.447
He doesn't want to go into Ephesus because he thinks that if he gets there and goes inside that city, it's going to detain him from being able to get out and really get to Jerusalem, which is his goal now.

02:37.807 --> 02:39.069
He's jingling his keys.

02:39.129 --> 02:40.610
He feels like he needs to be on the move.

02:40.850 --> 02:42.632
He's got to get to Jerusalem by Pentecost.

02:42.912 --> 02:45.234
That's going to be a challenge to do if he goes to Ephesus.

02:45.254 --> 02:46.615
So he says, Ephesus, you come to me.

02:46.955 --> 02:50.298
He calls the elders and summons them to come in chapter 20.

02:50.739 --> 02:52.260
And so he gives them, once they

02:52.240 --> 02:57.948
get there, probably two or three-day trip, he gives them this farewell address.

02:58.108 --> 03:07.081
And this moment is just pregnant with gravity, with sobriety, with affection.

03:07.942 --> 03:15.333
And Paul has these different movements that he's sort of commending his own example to them in verses 18 through 27.

03:15.413 --> 03:17.716
So there are almost three sorts of commendations.

03:18.096 --> 03:19.218
We could have really taught that

03:19.362 --> 03:20.283
the text in this way.

03:20.544 --> 03:31.360
He commends his own example to the Ephesian elders, then he commends the Ephesian elders to the task of caring for the Ephesian church, and then he commends the Ephesian church to the grace of God in verse 32-35.

03:32.802 --> 03:43.038
And so here in this text, as we read it in a second, you're gonna see it just be manifestly obvious that there are clear points of application for elders.

03:43.699 --> 03:48.626
That's the immediate audience that Paul is speaking to, so there's clear application for elders.

03:48.802 --> 03:52.867
But I think the application isn't necessarily confined to elders.

03:52.907 --> 03:57.573
Any more than the application of Proverbs 31 is confined to women who are married and have children.

03:57.933 --> 03:58.914
There's a way to apply.

03:58.934 --> 04:04.341
We're supposed to come away from every text of scripture with a means of applying that to our own lives.

04:04.581 --> 04:07.825
All scripture is profitable for all believers.

04:07.885 --> 04:18.258
And so there's a sense in which each one of us can come away from this text, even though it's specifically located, in the matrix of church leadership and eldership,

04:18.402 --> 04:23.788
Every one of us can come away with something, something to respond to by God's grace.

04:23.808 --> 04:29.675
And so I've kind of put some tracks there to activate and enable some tracks for us as we start at the top of your outline.

04:30.576 --> 04:33.218
So as we started this passage, listen for multiple tracks.

04:33.879 --> 04:35.641
So fellow elders, let's just start there.

04:36.002 --> 04:43.570
If you're an elder, one of the 35 brothers who serves as a pastor here at the Church of Prokils, I want to call you to listen to God's word.

04:44.290 --> 04:56.852
to listen to what this text says to us about what matters, about what our responsibility is before our God, what we will stand before Him and give account for how we've done these kinds of things.

04:56.872 --> 05:00.739
This gives us the shape and contours of pastoral ministry.

05:01.019 --> 05:05.407
So next, church members, and in relation to the previous point about eldership.

05:05.427 --> 05:09.394
So church members, as those placed by God,

05:09.794 --> 05:22.941
under the care of overseers, under the care of spiritual authorities of elders in the church, lean into the good design of God in providing spiritual oversight in the church.

05:22.982 --> 05:25.026
Don't resist spiritual oversight.

05:25.166 --> 05:25.848
Lean into it.

05:26.108 --> 05:30.898
And one of the ways in which we need you to lean into it is to pray for your pastors.

05:31.394 --> 05:38.524
I love the fact that Paul isn't ashamed at all to ask churches that he provides leadership for, to pray for us.

05:38.544 --> 05:42.128
He says, pray for us that the Word may speed ahead, pray for us.

05:42.549 --> 05:45.373
And so we need you, 35 elders, and I speak for all of them.

05:45.413 --> 05:46.454
I'm confident of this.

05:46.915 --> 05:48.797
We need your prayers.

05:49.899 --> 05:51.240
We are weak men.

05:51.401 --> 05:54.525
We are inadequate for the task that's before us.

05:54.545 --> 05:58.050
We can't do this in our own strength, in our own power.

05:58.130 --> 05:59.211
We need God's Spirit.

05:59.311 --> 06:01.394
We need your prayers.

06:02.018 --> 06:19.458
Third, those who are aspiring to elderships, so those of you who were maybe able to make it to the meeting last weekend, or maybe you weren't able to make it to the meeting last weekend, listen again and allow the Lord to refresh and update your sense of what it means to be an elder.

06:20.820 --> 06:26.226
And remember and recognize that the calling to eldership is not

06:26.434 --> 06:28.177
It is not about power.

06:28.418 --> 06:30.281
It is not about recognition.

06:30.341 --> 06:34.008
It is not about wielding change in policies of the church.

06:34.168 --> 06:41.161
It is about knowing the flock, feeding the flock, leading the flock, guarding the flock.

06:41.282 --> 06:43.145
That's what eldership is.

06:43.305 --> 06:45.910
And Paul doesn't let them forget what it's all about.

06:45.970 --> 06:48.736
These are the main things of biblical eldership.

06:48.796 --> 06:50.098
And lastly, all believers.

06:51.426 --> 06:57.493
all believe, realize as those called to make disciples, there's something for each one of us to take away from this passage.

06:57.513 --> 07:17.556
There's a way for us to ask God for strength and for power to manifest, to demonstrate something of this picture of initiative, of spiritual leadership, of mentoring, of outpouring our lives in the service of others, to strengthen, to bring them along in the faith.

07:17.576 --> 07:19.698
And so with that said, and those

07:19.906 --> 07:22.209
sort of channels activated and enabled.

07:22.250 --> 07:24.232
Let's listen to the text as we read God's word.

07:24.253 --> 07:30.161
I'm gonna read the broader context, even though we're gonna focus on just the first 10 or 12 verses.

07:31.123 --> 07:32.104
Beginning in verse 17.

07:35.469 --> 07:39.495
Now from my leaders, he sent to Ephesus and called the elders of the church to come to him.

07:40.497 --> 07:49.330
And when they came to him, he said to them, you yourselves know how I lived among you the whole time from the first day that I set foot in Asia.

07:49.858 --> 07:57.005
serving the Lord with all humility and with tears and with trials that happened to me through the plots of the Jews.

07:58.266 --> 08:11.039
How I did not shrink from declaring to you anything that was profitable and teaching you in public and from house to house, testifying both to Jews and to Greeks of repentance toward God and of faith in our Lord Jesus Christ.

08:11.059 --> 08:13.962
So here he is, commending his example to them, verse 22.

08:14.362 --> 08:17.906
And now, behold, I am going to Jerusalem

08:18.050 --> 08:27.546
constrained by the Spirit, not knowing what will happen to me there, except that the Holy Spirit testifies to me in every city that imprisonment and afflictions await me.

08:28.347 --> 08:33.035
But I do not account my life of any value, nor is precious to myself.

08:33.737 --> 08:44.114
If only I may finish my course in the ministry that I received from the Lord Jesus to testify to the gospel of the grace of God.

08:44.930 --> 08:54.444
And now, behold, I know that none of you among whom I have gone out, excuse me, whom I have gone about proclaiming the kingdom will see my face again.

08:54.504 --> 09:05.399
Therefore, I testify to you this day that I am innocent of the blood of all, for I did not shrink from declaring to you the whole counsel of God."

09:05.459 --> 09:10.066
That's his commending his own example, and now he commends them to the church.

09:10.370 --> 09:20.545
Pay careful attention to yourselves and to all the flock in which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers to care for the Church of God, which he obtained with his own blood.

09:21.607 --> 09:31.922
I know that after my departure, fierce wolves will come in among you, not sparing the flock, and from among your own selves will arise men, speaking twisted things to draw away the disciples after them.

09:32.303 --> 09:34.546
Therefore, be alert.

09:35.394 --> 09:42.044
remembering that for three years, I did not cease night or day to admonish everyone with tears.

09:42.124 --> 09:44.588
And now he commends the church to the grace of God.

09:44.648 --> 09:54.142
Now I commend you to God and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up and to give you the inheritance among all those who are sanctified.

09:54.483 --> 09:57.167
I coveted no one silver or gold or apparel.

09:57.507 --> 10:01.874
You yourselves know that these hands ministered to my necessities and to those who were with me.

10:02.114 --> 10:13.585
In all things I have shown you that by working hard in this way, we must help the weak and remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how He Himself said, it is more blessed to give than to receive.

10:17.169 --> 10:18.230
Some things never change.

10:21.232 --> 10:21.913
And some things do.

10:22.013 --> 10:31.122
As time moves on, methods of gospel advance may change and they're not the same in every age, they're not the same necessarily in every

10:31.362 --> 10:33.445
culture, but some things never change.

10:33.505 --> 10:39.753
The world essentially hasn't changed since the time that Paul spoke these words 2000 years ago.

10:39.813 --> 10:40.935
The idols are the same.

10:40.955 --> 10:45.301
They're dressed up differently, but they're the same idols.

10:46.963 --> 10:50.788
The nature of the work of the mission of the gospel is the same.

10:50.848 --> 10:54.914
The nature of the work of the church, the message that we have for the world.

10:54.974 --> 10:55.955
That's the same.

10:57.517 --> 11:00.882
The nature of the ministry in the world is essentially

11:01.378 --> 11:01.819
the same.

11:02.539 --> 11:14.534
And so Acts 20 is Paul speaking to church leaders and he's talking about the essence of ministry, the essence of spiritual leadership, the work of ministry in the church.

11:14.554 --> 11:27.250
And so he's bringing up themes that we haven't heard much of in the book of Acts because Acts has so largely been missional, pioneering work, advancing, planting churches, speaking to unreached peoples and

11:27.426 --> 11:29.751
communicating the gospel by way of evangelism.

11:29.831 --> 11:37.847
These are some new themes, and these are themes that Paul is going to drop into with great energy as he writes to the churches in later days.

11:37.927 --> 11:42.517
In coming days, five, six, seven years ahead, he's going to start writing books, Ephesians and Philippians.

11:42.537 --> 11:49.010
He's already written Galatians, but he's about to drive out a number of letters to different leaders in the church, Timothy Titus.

11:49.314 --> 11:50.757
and churches themselves.

11:51.057 --> 12:00.173
And so he's bringing up a sort of preview into pastoral ministry and themes that he's going to talk about for the rest of his life until he dies about 10 years from now.

12:00.915 --> 12:06.344
And so here in Acts 20, he's talking about stuff that matters in pastoral ministry, the grace of God.

12:06.364 --> 12:09.490
He talks about the kingdom and purposes and plans of God.

12:10.466 --> 12:15.332
He speaks about the centrality of the message of repentance and faith in Jesus Christ.

12:15.733 --> 12:22.441
He charges the elders here to care for the flock of God, to care for the church at Ephesus.

12:22.461 --> 12:28.849
These are themes that he's gonna be just weaving through all of his letters, all of his pastoral admonishment.

12:28.889 --> 12:31.272
He talks here about suffering and hardship in the church.

12:31.292 --> 12:35.057
He's talking about wolves and false teachers who are coming and doing their work.

12:35.137 --> 12:39.442
He talks about running the race of faith and finishing your course.

12:40.130 --> 12:45.056
He talks about the eternal inheritance that is stored up for the saints in Christ.

12:46.218 --> 12:50.983
These are prominent themes that he's gonna unpack more fully in his letters to the churches.

12:51.024 --> 13:01.657
And so if you're there in my leaders as some of the elders who have traveled up from Ephesus, you are at this moment pushing to the end of your seat.

13:01.677 --> 13:03.099
This is a farewell address.

13:03.139 --> 13:09.106
If you've read other farewell addresses in scripture, you know this is a moment of great significance.

13:10.114 --> 13:20.428
Jacob's last moments with his sons in Genesis 49, Moses last words in Deuteronomy, Joshua's last words, Samuel's last words, Jesus last words in John 13 through 17.

13:20.669 --> 13:23.172
This is a moment pregnant with significance.

13:23.793 --> 13:26.577
And so they're leaning all the way, all the way in.

13:26.797 --> 13:29.742
And Paul knows he's leaving and he's never going to see these guys again.

13:29.782 --> 13:30.803
He says that in verse 25.

13:31.043 --> 13:32.225
I'm going to board a ship.

13:32.465 --> 13:33.867
You'll never see my face again.

13:34.068 --> 13:35.730
And so he doesn't have time to talk about the weather.

13:35.970 --> 13:38.674
He's going to talk about stuff that matters for eternity.

13:39.490 --> 13:44.336
He's gonna talk about the church, how to care for the church.

13:44.356 --> 13:52.205
He's gonna talk about spiritual ambition and priorities in ministry, pouring oneself out in the service of the church of Jesus Christ.

13:52.285 --> 13:55.149
He wants to prepare them for challenges on the horizon.

13:55.369 --> 14:02.938
He wants to tell them a little bit of what's around the corner based on 25 years of scars and experience that he's gained by this point in ministry.

14:04.039 --> 14:05.481
They're pushing to the end of their seats.

14:05.501 --> 14:06.482
And so as we listen,

14:07.586 --> 14:10.329
We can learn something about the entailments of spiritual leadership.

14:10.349 --> 14:13.011
Number one, it's a call to serve the Lord.

14:14.653 --> 14:15.754
It's a call to serve the Lord.

14:15.774 --> 14:20.919
And what a picture of servanthood we have here in this text, beginning right there in verse 18.

14:21.280 --> 14:21.980
Look at verse 18.

14:22.861 --> 14:32.711
He said to them, you yourselves know how I lived among you the whole time from the first day that I set foot in Asia.

14:33.412 --> 14:34.373
Don't you love that?

14:34.573 --> 14:35.794
Paul's feet.

14:35.874 --> 14:41.743
land on Asian soil, and he's all in, in serving the church.

14:42.644 --> 14:47.371
All in, in equipping and training, ethicists, and discipling them in the Word.

14:47.611 --> 14:49.634
And he says, how I lived among you.

14:49.775 --> 14:52.539
Peter emphasizes this later on toward the end of Peter's life.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.441
He says the same thing to elders.

14:54.482 --> 15:01.292
In first Peter chapter five, I exhort you as a fellow elder to shepherd the flock of God.

15:01.312 --> 15:03.595
He says, that is among you.

15:04.076 --> 15:05.618
Shepherds smell like

15:05.794 --> 15:08.878
sheep, because they're among sheep.

15:09.419 --> 15:12.122
Paul is not some ivory tower theologian.

15:12.182 --> 15:14.204
He's in among the people.

15:14.224 --> 15:15.586
He says, you saw my life.

15:15.626 --> 15:16.688
He says this over and over.

15:16.888 --> 15:18.129
You saw how I worked.

15:18.169 --> 15:22.955
He says, what you've seen and learned from me and heard from me, practice these things.

15:23.015 --> 15:24.938
And the God of peace will be with you.

15:24.958 --> 15:27.241
He says, imitate me as I imitate Christ.

15:27.281 --> 15:30.385
You can't imitate someone you've never seen, somebody who lives in the green room.

15:30.725 --> 15:32.707
He says, you've known my life.

15:32.768 --> 15:33.869
I've lived among you.

15:33.909 --> 15:34.770
I've served.

15:34.946 --> 15:38.470
Among you, He came all the way into the fellowship.

15:38.490 --> 15:46.039
There's a proximity in spiritual leadership that is required, a proximity to the people that we're called to care for.

15:46.419 --> 15:55.249
And we're not just closed, we're closed with a vision and a heart to serve, not to be served with a heart to serve.

15:55.289 --> 15:57.572
Jesus talked about this, He clarified His mission.

15:58.533 --> 16:03.218
This is the King who comes and He says, let me clarify why I'm here, not here to be served, I'm here to serve.

16:04.034 --> 16:05.776
to give my life as a ransom for many.

16:05.796 --> 16:10.360
And then he says later on, and I've left you an example that you might follow in my footsteps.

16:10.761 --> 16:14.384
The Greek word for ministry is Diaconia.

16:14.564 --> 16:16.827
It means table service.

16:18.088 --> 16:19.890
Ministry is service.

16:21.551 --> 16:26.176
Ministry is not contrary to so many things that we see in our culture.

16:26.256 --> 16:28.318
It is not self-promotion.

16:28.718 --> 16:30.800
It is not ego on parade.

16:30.940 --> 16:32.562
It is service.

16:33.250 --> 16:35.232
to Christ's people, service to the church.

16:35.252 --> 16:43.179
He summarizes, Paul summarizes 25 years of ministry and three years in Ephesus in particular with three words in verse 19.

16:45.101 --> 16:46.403
Serving the Lord.

16:48.625 --> 16:49.245
Serving the Lord.

16:51.487 --> 16:52.568
Notice the context though.

16:53.229 --> 16:54.871
The context in which he talks about the service.

16:55.491 --> 17:02.578
This serving the Lord says nothing about Paul's private worship, his private prayer life, his private time in the Word.

17:02.658 --> 17:08.468
In other words, his service, this passage speaks of Paul's service to God in terms of his service to the church.

17:09.671 --> 17:13.618
It's a very tangible, concrete means by which he serves God.

17:13.798 --> 17:16.363
You ask the question, Paul, how are you serving the Lord?

17:16.383 --> 17:18.867
That's such a sort of foggy concept.

17:19.168 --> 17:20.470
How are you serving the Lord?

17:20.570 --> 17:24.978
Paul's answer, verse 20, is I serve the Lord by declaring what's profitable.

17:25.602 --> 17:28.385
I serve the Lord by teaching in public and from house to house.

17:28.666 --> 17:34.833
I serve the Lord verse 21 by testifying to the importance of repentance toward God and faith in our Lord Jesus Christ.

17:34.853 --> 17:36.695
His service is tangible.

17:37.136 --> 17:41.962
His service to God is rendered through and by means of service to the church.

17:44.765 --> 17:53.616
The epistle of first John loves to think of ministry in this kind of hard knock on it, tangible kind of way.

17:54.397 --> 17:55.218
When John writes,

17:55.874 --> 18:02.841
He who does not love his brother whom he has seen, cannot love God whom he has not seen."

18:04.503 --> 18:05.144
What does that mean?

18:05.204 --> 18:12.952
In other words, just because the God we worship is invisible to our eyes, doesn't mean that our service to him is invisible in the world.

18:14.394 --> 18:16.116
It's visible service.

18:16.236 --> 18:22.002
Our love for an invisible God, the invisible God, is demonstrated by loving people who are standing in front of us.

18:22.786 --> 18:29.713
It's a tangible love, a tangible service to people which redounds to the glory of God.

18:29.853 --> 18:33.817
It's ultimately for God.

18:33.837 --> 18:35.899
This is the means by which Paul is serving the Lord.

18:35.919 --> 18:41.264
So we see not only the actions of Paul serving the Lord, but the attitude.

18:42.485 --> 18:43.366
How does he serve the Lord?

18:43.386 --> 18:51.474
He says, serving the Lord verse 19 with all humility.

18:51.554 --> 18:56.361
The tone, the demeanor of Paul's service was humble.

18:57.964 --> 18:59.546
It was self forgetting.

18:59.646 --> 19:01.329
It was others focused.

19:01.409 --> 19:02.591
He served with all humility.

19:02.611 --> 19:03.933
That doesn't mean Paul was a pushover.

19:04.694 --> 19:05.936
Doesn't mean he was a low talker.

19:05.956 --> 19:09.682
You always had to ask him to speak up because, you know, he probably didn't think that what he said meant much.

19:10.303 --> 19:11.825
It doesn't mean any of those kinds of things.

19:11.865 --> 19:17.874
We sort of associate humility with external things that have precious little to do with humility, really.

19:18.594 --> 19:22.799
Doesn't mean that every other thing that came out of Paul's mouth was something bad about himself.

19:22.859 --> 19:23.941
It doesn't mean any of that.

19:23.961 --> 19:25.002
It's not humble speak.

19:25.823 --> 19:26.864
He wasn't a pushover.

19:27.525 --> 19:28.526
Read Acts 15.

19:29.487 --> 19:30.469
He knows how to stand up.

19:30.509 --> 19:32.571
He wasn't always quiet.

19:32.591 --> 19:34.514
He was fairly loud in the book of Galatians.

19:35.475 --> 19:35.835
Read him.

19:36.856 --> 19:38.779
