20:14.353 --> 20:15.635
I remember going up and singing a special.

20:15.855 --> 20:19.641
For those of you who have come to faith recently, you don't know what singing a special means.

20:20.542 --> 20:21.223
One, you're welcome.

20:21.363 --> 20:24.267
Two, I can explain it later.

20:24.348 --> 20:37.426
But anyway, so I sang a special, you know, chord in hand, cue it up, start the song, sang the special, and then at the end of the meeting, one of my parents' friends came up and just said, that was a great job, buddy.

20:37.794 --> 20:39.957
And I didn't know what to say, which is very awkward.

20:40.137 --> 20:43.021
And so I just used a phrase I had heard other people saying, I said, it was all God.

20:43.902 --> 20:46.145
And he said it was good, but it wasn't that good.

20:46.165 --> 20:53.154
And he just kind of poked me in the arm, which is his way of just saying, Matt, don't be super spiritual.

20:54.316 --> 20:55.297
Thanks is fine.

20:56.158 --> 21:05.170
Just receive encouragement so we can overcompensate and create really what is just pretended false fake humility and name and in word.

21:05.346 --> 21:05.747
only.

21:06.268 --> 21:10.054
But there's no air of false modesty in Paul.

21:10.074 --> 21:11.076
There's no false humility.

21:11.096 --> 21:15.003
Matter of fact, he's able to say, I serve the Lord with all humility.

21:15.023 --> 21:16.225
That doesn't sound very humble.

21:16.586 --> 21:18.088
Well, he's not afraid to say that.

21:18.409 --> 21:21.234
That's what I've aimed at doing the entire time that I was there.

21:22.626 --> 21:29.441
Paul is clear that there's no false modesty, but he is constantly trying to reorient the people that he leads.

21:29.781 --> 21:37.538
He's constantly trying to show them that my whole life, everything that I say and everything that I do, I want to demonstrate that leadership asserts.

21:38.500 --> 21:39.382
That's what leadership is.

21:40.745 --> 21:43.090
And he really has to clarify that, especially in Corinth.

21:43.778 --> 21:48.082
Because in Corinth, they have this group of men called the super apostles, and they seem really awesome.

21:48.102 --> 21:49.744
And Paul comes with weakness and trembling.

21:49.764 --> 21:53.768
His letters are powerful, but he comes and he doesn't look like much when he stands in front of us.

21:54.729 --> 22:01.016
And Paul is trying to reorient them, and he finds out in the very opening chapter of his letter to Corinth, his first letter to Corinth.

22:01.316 --> 22:07.923
He says, why are you people saying things like, I am of Paul, I am of Cephas, I am of Apollos?

22:07.963 --> 22:09.224
And he asks a pointed question.

22:09.264 --> 22:10.866
He says, was Paul crucified for you?

22:12.322 --> 22:14.085
Were you baptized into the name of Paul?

22:16.649 --> 22:17.551
He's clarifying that.

22:17.571 --> 22:24.182
He goes on to say, when you think of your leaders, he says this in 1 Corinthians 3, 5, what then is Apollos?

22:24.863 --> 22:25.705
What is Paul?

22:26.005 --> 22:33.057
Answer servants, do laws, slaves, bond servants, servants through whom you believe.

22:33.117 --> 22:33.618
