22:33.762 --> 22:36.165
We poured water on stuff and God made it grow.

22:36.205 --> 22:37.167
That's all we did.

22:37.227 --> 22:39.430
We were servants for Jesus' sake.

22:39.450 --> 22:40.652
We didn't preach ourselves.

22:40.732 --> 22:41.994
We preached Christ.

22:42.034 --> 22:47.001
In other words, Paul is saying very clearly, when you think of your leaders, think of us as servants first.

22:47.601 --> 22:55.052
Even the metaphors that he chooses when he unpacks this point in 1 Corinthians 3 are metaphors of everyday life, mundane life.

22:55.092 --> 22:56.754
You just think of us in overalls.

22:56.794 --> 22:57.756
We're farm hands.

22:58.777 --> 23:00.099
We're construction workers.

23:00.219 --> 23:02.322
We put bricks on a house.

23:03.170 --> 23:04.131
We poor cement.

23:04.151 --> 23:05.293
That's what we do.

23:05.893 --> 23:07.075
It's everyday kind of work.

23:07.155 --> 23:08.857
It's service to the body.

23:09.958 --> 23:15.545
Paul comes in just as he opens the door, as it were, through his letters in Romans 1, verse 1.

23:15.846 --> 23:19.270
Paul, a servant of Christ Jesus, called to be an apostle.

23:20.431 --> 23:21.212
Philippians 1, 1.

23:21.532 --> 23:26.318
Paul and Timothy, servants, doula, slaves of Christ Jesus, Titus 1, 1.

23:26.418 --> 23:29.903
Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ.

23:30.243 --> 23:31.985
They're not superstars.

23:32.005 --> 23:32.626
They're servants.

23:34.114 --> 23:42.949
I remember hearing a conversation that was had between John Piper and a member of the Desiring God staff many years ago and Piper referenced this at a conference.

23:44.391 --> 23:57.874
And he said we were talking and this guy who worked on the staff there was telling him about name the name of a preacher who had planted a church in the Northwest and Piper said I've never heard of him tell me more about him and the

23:58.050 --> 24:10.503
The staffer said, oh, he's one of the up-and-coming sort of rising stars in evangelicalism and Piper exhorted this young man and said, let's not be a people who use the language of stardom when we talk about ministers.

24:12.285 --> 24:13.627
Let's not build that.

24:13.707 --> 24:23.117
Let's not cultivate a culture of celebrity among those who preach the gospel, who serve the churches.

24:23.217 --> 24:24.498
Paul serves with humility.

24:26.786 --> 24:27.467
I love how C.S.

24:27.507 --> 24:28.568
Lewis describes humility.

24:28.608 --> 24:29.088
He says this.

24:30.790 --> 24:36.817
Do not imagine that if you meet a really humble man, he will be what most people call humble nowadays.

24:37.918 --> 24:43.383
He will not be a sort of greasy, smarmy person who is always telling you that, of course, he is nobody.

24:44.445 --> 24:51.392
Probably all you will think about him is that he seemed a cheerful, intelligent chap who took a real interest in what you said to him.

24:52.233 --> 24:53.394
If you do dislike him,

24:53.506 --> 24:57.932
It will be because you feel a little envious of anyone who seems to enjoy life so easily.

24:58.573 --> 25:00.175
He will not be thinking about humility.

25:00.776 --> 25:03.200
He will not be thinking about himself at all.

25:04.842 --> 25:10.009
But Lewis is suggesting here, I love this quote because he's suggesting that we don't aim at humility directly.

25:11.491 --> 25:13.394
We focus on other people.

25:14.146 --> 25:15.447
We pray for other people.

25:15.487 --> 25:17.169
We give thanks for other people.

25:17.590 --> 25:37.572
So it's a humility is a byproduct of seeing God as he is and focusing on serving others, giving people our undivided attention, listening well to people, praying for others, giving thanks for others, and what ends up happening incidentally, whether we notice it or not, hopefully not, is humility begins to be cultivated in our hearts.

25:37.592 --> 25:43.218
So the call to spiritual leadership is a call to serve the Lord by serving brothers and sisters.

25:43.586 --> 25:47.290
in all humility and second with tears.

25:47.390 --> 25:47.890
You see that?

25:48.451 --> 25:54.437
Verse 19, serving the Lord with all humility and with tears.

25:56.319 --> 25:57.541
I remember who this Paul is.

25:57.561 --> 26:10.514
This is the same Paul who says in Romans, I could wish that I would be a cursed for the sake of my kinsmen Israel, knowing Christ.

26:12.738 --> 26:14.863
He's pleading with his kinsmen.

26:14.883 --> 26:21.156
This is the same Paul who says that he's daily weighed down with the pressures of the well-being of the churches that he serves.

26:21.176 --> 26:29.234
This is the same Paul who labors night and day, who labors, he says to the Galatian believers, until Christ be formed in you.

26:29.282 --> 26:50.594
passion, this beating heart of affection and love for his people, the same Paul who doesn't cease to give thanks and making mention to God of the people in Philippi, the believers in Philippi, he's constantly remembering them in his prayers, the same Paul who calls the church at Thessalonica, the believers there, his joy and his crown.

26:52.857 --> 26:53.458
Powerful.

26:54.082 --> 26:58.708
The same Paul who in that same letter, 1 Thessalonians says, I sent Timothy to you.

26:58.988 --> 27:04.776
I personally couldn't get there Satan hindered me, but I sent Timothy because I had to know how you're fairing.

27:05.136 --> 27:05.877
How are you doing?

27:06.078 --> 27:07.500
And Timothy brought back good news.

27:07.680 --> 27:08.801
And so I'm alive again.

27:10.804 --> 27:13.768
He even goes on to say, use those very same kind of words.

27:13.788 --> 27:18.514
He says, we live if you stand fast in the Lord.

27:18.946 --> 27:25.672
He uses the metaphor that he uses to talk about his service and his care for the church is a metaphor of the greatest possible tenderness.

27:25.953 --> 27:35.622
He says, we were gentle among you like a nursing mother taking care of her own children.

27:35.642 --> 27:48.434
With humility, with tears, there's this close knit relationship, this love, this affection, you read Philippians, you read Galatians, read Thessalonians, they aren't clinical in tone.

27:49.378 --> 27:51.261
They don't smell of the classroom.

27:51.301 --> 27:54.685
It is Paul loving, hugging, embracing.

27:54.745 --> 27:56.808
There's affection.

27:56.828 --> 27:58.491
There's strong exhortation.

27:58.511 --> 28:02.396
There's profuse encouragement in these letters.

28:03.297 --> 28:04.719
And where's Paul getting that model?

28:04.739 --> 28:06.261
He's getting it from Jesus himself.

28:08.064 --> 28:10.187
Think about Jesus' service to the body.

28:10.247 --> 28:12.430
Jesus comes in and he's not detached.

28:12.450 --> 28:17.297
He's not lobbing evangelism tracks into Palestine.

28:17.317 --> 28:18.258
He comes

28:18.466 --> 28:24.312
To the people where they are, Hebrew says, he came as a sympathetic high priest.

28:24.352 --> 28:26.214
He was touched by our infirmities.

28:26.414 --> 28:28.816
He wept when he heard that Lazarus was dead.

28:29.117 --> 28:32.000
He touched people and let them touch him back.

28:33.481 --> 28:34.482
He was affectionate.

28:34.562 --> 28:35.643
He was broken.

28:37.265 --> 28:41.649
He broke over, I'm just straight up broke over Jerusalem.

28:42.330 --> 28:43.771
Jerusalem, Jerusalem.

28:45.073 --> 28:46.514
How I have longed.

28:46.818 --> 28:51.705
to gather you like a hen gathers her chicks, but you just wouldn't come.

28:51.745 --> 28:55.791
You're just resisting me all day long, and you're resisting life.

28:56.091 --> 28:58.515
Come to me that you might have life.

29:00.357 --> 29:03.001
Not come to seek to steal, kill, and destroy.

29:03.201 --> 29:04.283
Come that you might have life.

29:04.303 --> 29:06.146
He's inviting people all over the place.

29:06.486 --> 29:12.675
Samaritan, prostitutes, tax collectors, losers, sellouts, tired, weary, sinful people.

29:12.695 --> 29:14.738
He's saying, come to me, all of you.

29:16.546 --> 29:18.169
Heavy laden, I will give you rest."

29:18.189 --> 29:20.133
He wasn't a professional minister.

29:22.978 --> 29:24.120
He wasn't above pleading.

29:25.703 --> 29:26.404
Neither was Paul.

29:27.767 --> 29:40.210
And they stand in a long line of weeping prophets, Jeremiah and Isaiah and Peter and Paul and Stephen and Barnabas, weeping prophets, tearful

29:40.706 --> 29:41.086
prophet.

29:41.187 --> 29:52.640
Spiritual leadership is a call to serve the Lord with humility, it's a call to serve the Lord with tears, and it's a call to die to self.

29:52.660 --> 29:53.601
A call to die to self.

29:53.621 --> 29:54.342
Look at verse 22.

29:56.945 --> 30:04.274
And now behold, I'm going to Jerusalem constrained by the spirit, not knowing what will happen to me there, except

30:05.346 --> 30:09.291
that the Holy Spirit testifies to me in every city that imprisonment and afflictions await me.

30:09.311 --> 30:10.693
So apart from that, I don't know anything.

30:11.034 --> 30:12.856
It's just gonna be really hard, right?

30:13.998 --> 30:34.546
But, verse 24, I do not account my life of any value, nor as precious to myself if only I may finish my course, as highest ambition, and the ministry that I received from the Lord Jesus to testify to the gospel

30:34.626 --> 30:36.529
of the grace of God.

30:38.232 --> 30:39.894
Oh, what a wonderful verse to pray.

30:40.094 --> 31:03.090
Last year, I chose seven verses to pray for one on each day of the week, and the one that was on Wednesday was Acts 20, verse 24, just spent a whole year, just Wednesday after Wednesday, just praying this into my heart, desiring this for my life, praying this for my family members, praying this for friends, just looking down my prayer list and just going,

31:03.330 --> 31:06.094
finger on this verse, finger on the list, and just praying this.

31:07.075 --> 31:13.583
It will be faithful, testifying to the gospel of the grace of God.

31:13.643 --> 31:16.788
Ministry is not about self-promotion.

31:18.710 --> 31:24.818
Ministry is an expression of self-sacrificing love toward others, or it's worthless.

31:24.994 --> 31:26.496
language in 1 Corinthians 13.

31:27.497 --> 31:28.298
He says, you know what it is?

31:28.378 --> 31:32.383
If you go out and you serve and you do all these things, it's just clanging symbols.

31:32.443 --> 31:40.693
If it's not motivated by love, you're just making a lot of racket to draw attention to yourself, but there's no genuine heart of ministry because it's not motivated by love.

31:41.534 --> 31:48.203
Therefore, its value is nil, not for Paul.

31:48.223 --> 31:49.164
He leaned all the way in.

31:49.204 --> 31:54.290
He was all in for God's purposes and sharing and serving his brothers and sisters.

31:57.026 --> 31:58.808
He's dying to himself that they might live.

31:58.828 --> 32:05.015
When I was a teenager, I started to sense the beginnings of a call to ministry.

32:05.075 --> 32:09.540
And so I was cultivating conversation.

32:09.580 --> 32:13.144
My dad had died already, so couldn't ask him questions about ministry.

32:13.184 --> 32:16.307
But whenever I was around other pastors, I was just asking questions to them.

32:16.327 --> 32:17.789
And so I remember going on a mission strip.

32:18.289 --> 32:20.011
I think it was my first mission strip to Mexico.

32:20.892 --> 32:26.098
And sitting next to a guy on the bus, and he was the pastor of a church just down the street from the one where I was,

32:26.498 --> 32:36.176
And I was just asking him tons and tons of questions and the more I talked to him, the more I was blown away by his knowledge and his boldness.

32:36.637 --> 32:39.442
I never heard a guy say the kinds of things that he was willing to say.

32:39.482 --> 32:46.254
And so there was tremendous boldness and just tremendous knowledge and wit and just force a personality, almost knock you over.

32:46.415 --> 32:50.482
And then the more I sat next to members from his congregation,

32:50.850 --> 32:55.858
The more I was impressed with the fact that it seemed like he had assembled an entire church full of biblical scholars.

32:56.198 --> 33:00.765
I mean, everybody was so impressive in how much they knew about the Bible.

33:01.086 --> 33:05.793
And so I sat down with him and we just found ourselves alone together and I said, so what do you do?

33:06.133 --> 33:08.517
Your people all love the word so much.

33:08.557 --> 33:16.048
What is it that makes them so want to go after this and even debate each other on the bus and talk about theology?

33:17.130 --> 33:19.794
And he said, and I'll never forget it, word for word.

33:19.970 --> 33:20.691
at least part of it.

33:20.771 --> 33:31.703
He said, Matt, one of the things you have to do to build well, to build a healthy church is you have to, quote, inject a healthy dose of cynicism into your congregation.

33:34.086 --> 33:41.874
That struck me as odd, but a lot of the things you had already said were so bold and so odd that I just kind of took it at face value and said, okay, I'll just think about that.

33:41.914 --> 33:43.876
I thought about it for 20-something years.

33:44.857 --> 33:49.042
Now, and now as I look back, it's no surprise that he split the church about four years later.

33:50.370 --> 33:59.160
And he announced it on the day up, just showed up at the service, an hour from where I was, showed up at his service, announced that he was gone and preached a message on apostasy.

34:00.461 --> 34:06.788
And then he went on his Christian radio program and used the airwaves to blast the church and completely throw it under the bus.

34:06.868 --> 34:10.572
And I ended up serving on staff at that church for 10 years before moving here.

34:11.413 --> 34:19.442
And I heard sad, sad story after sad story after sad story about the impact of that kind of

34:19.554 --> 34:32.932
cynical ministry and people about how he would come to staff meeting and he would laugh and he would throw his Bible on the table and he would point at some hard text in the Bible and say, I'm going to get them this week.

34:32.952 --> 34:33.273
Get them.

34:35.536 --> 34:35.996
Get them.

34:38.360 --> 34:40.963
That's not feeding the sheep.

34:40.983 --> 34:43.126
That's not laying down your life for the sheep.

34:43.146 --> 34:44.188
That's hunting the sheep.

34:45.569 --> 34:46.791
That's not pastoral care.

34:46.811 --> 34:48.914
That's not pastoral ministry.

34:48.994 --> 34:52.018
That's ego flying under the banner of prophetic zeal.

34:52.118 --> 34:57.165
And it's all too easy and all too tempting for leaders of all kinds to fall into that.

34:58.327 --> 35:01.311
But Paul shows us, friends, he shows us a better way.

35:02.332 --> 35:07.199
Paul even says to Corinth in 2 Corinthians, he says, I don't enjoy saying hard things to you.

35:07.239 --> 35:08.821
I get no kicks out of that.

35:08.862 --> 35:10.083
I don't have a smirk on my face.

35:10.143 --> 35:13.488
It breaks my heart to say the things I had to say to you in the last letter.

35:14.289 --> 35:15.831
He gets no joy out of that.

35:17.153 --> 35:17.874
He says it.

35:17.954 --> 35:22.782
When he says it, when he brings correction, he does it because he has to to be faithful, not because he likes it.

35:25.848 --> 35:30.316
Paul shows us the spirit of Christ in ministry in that way.

35:30.496 --> 35:34.683
How did Christ treat the flock?

35:34.703 --> 35:36.306
He went out and found his lost sheep.

35:37.378 --> 35:38.319
He built a fold.

35:38.339 --> 35:40.663
He brought us into his fold.

35:40.963 --> 35:44.087
He led them by quiet streams, right, in green pastures.

35:44.107 --> 35:45.249
This is what Jesus does.

35:45.269 --> 35:47.332
Psalm 23, that's what Jesus does.

35:47.372 --> 35:48.493
He cares for his flock.

35:48.513 --> 35:51.538
He stays awake and keeps the wolves away while they're asleep.

35:51.558 --> 35:56.344
He chases them when they wander off and they find themselves out, lost somewhere.

35:56.665 --> 35:58.127
He spares no pains.

35:58.187 --> 35:58.988
He finds them.

35:59.048 --> 35:59.809
He tracks them.

35:59.869 --> 36:01.651
He brings them all the way back to the fold.

36:01.892 --> 36:06.418
He says at the end of his life, he says in John, Shepherd 10, I lay down my life.

36:06.594 --> 36:11.719
for the sheep, and he wants to be super clear, so he says, no one takes it from me.

36:12.820 --> 36:14.522
I lay it down on purpose.

36:14.542 --> 36:16.524
I lay it down of my own accord.

36:17.285 --> 36:18.306
Nobody takes it from me.

36:18.346 --> 36:20.027
I give it for them, for the sheep.

36:20.328 --> 36:21.749
That's true ministry.

36:21.769 --> 36:22.750
That's where Paul gets it from.

36:22.790 --> 36:24.152
That's spiritual leadership.

36:24.192 --> 36:25.193
That's dying to self.

36:28.976 --> 36:29.857
Out of love for others.

36:30.718 --> 36:33.241
Dying to self, out of love for others.

36:33.261 --> 36:34.482
You look at the pains.

36:35.394 --> 36:37.616
that Paul was taken for the church at Ephesus.

36:37.636 --> 36:38.437
Look at verse 20.

36:41.620 --> 36:45.183
So with tears, with trials, the universe 19, that happened to me through the positive of the Jews.

36:45.664 --> 36:51.229
How I did not shrink from declaring to you anything that was profitable.

36:51.509 --> 36:54.192
Anything that I saw that might help you, I brought it.

36:54.492 --> 36:56.935
Anything that could be to your prophet, I brought it.

36:57.535 --> 36:58.836
Paul said, we work.

36:58.876 --> 37:00.118
He's clarifying what leaders do.

37:00.138 --> 37:02.620
He says, we work, 2 Corinthians 1, 24.

37:03.141 --> 37:04.722
We work for your joy.

37:05.922 --> 37:07.584
That's the model of spiritual leadership.

37:07.804 --> 37:08.685
You work for us.

37:09.446 --> 37:10.327
You make us look good.

37:10.347 --> 37:11.268
You're our trophy church.

37:11.668 --> 37:12.489
It's not that.

37:12.930 --> 37:14.912
We work for you, not you work for us.

37:14.992 --> 37:17.415
Paul describes his ministry in that way in 2 Corinthians.

37:17.775 --> 37:19.537
He says, this is ministry for Paul.

37:19.657 --> 37:20.558
Paul, what is ministry?

37:20.859 --> 37:25.043
It's this, always caring about in our body the dying of Jesus.

37:26.785 --> 37:27.286
To what end?

37:27.346 --> 37:34.834
So then he says, Corinth, death is at work at us, but life is at work in you.

37:36.258 --> 37:36.979
We get to die.

37:38.000 --> 37:40.443
You get to live.

37:40.463 --> 37:42.746
That's spiritual leadership.

37:42.786 --> 37:43.386
That's care.

37:43.427 --> 37:44.848
That's pastoral care.

37:44.868 --> 37:49.374
Paul says in 1 Thessalonians 3, for now we live some of my favorite words.

37:49.854 --> 37:53.559
Now we live if you are standing fast in the Lord.

37:54.379 --> 38:00.086
In other words, Paul is saying, no matter what hardships we endure today, if you're standing firm in the faith, today was a good day.

38:01.388 --> 38:03.250
