38:04.290 --> 38:05.412
That's our greatest concern.

38:05.492 --> 38:06.513
This is love for the church.

38:06.573 --> 38:08.316
This is care for the church.

38:08.897 --> 38:09.157
C.S.

38:09.197 --> 38:14.966
Lewis says this, and it needs to be heard so desperately today in our culture of ministry.

38:16.348 --> 38:16.608
C.S.

38:16.648 --> 38:28.846
Lewis writes, I wish they'd remember that the charge to Peter was feed my sheep, not try experiments on my rats, or even teach my performing dogs new tricks.

38:30.869 --> 38:34.194
Feed my sheep.

38:34.338 --> 38:34.999
my lambs.

38:35.239 --> 38:54.640
This perspective on pastoral ministry means that spiritual leaders are prepared to be patient, are prepared to cultivate, are prepared to just wait and gently blow on the embers of the dying embers of faith and pray for fire.

38:55.742 --> 38:58.324
Pastors are loved to do this stuff.

39:01.328 --> 39:03.410
Spiritual leaders die divisions of grandeur.

39:06.242 --> 39:15.296
The trophy kids, trophy saints, trophy churches, called to die to self out of love for others, and to do this, finally, because Jesus is Lord.

39:17.820 --> 39:19.823
Because Jesus is Lord, look at verse 24.

39:19.843 --> 39:25.291
I do not account my life of any value, nor is precious to myself.

39:26.674 --> 39:34.706
If only I may finish my course and the ministry that I received from the Lord Jesus.

39:34.946 --> 39:36.408
That's the bottom line.

39:36.828 --> 39:45.979
That explains everything, all the beatings, all the suffering, all the pressing on and being tenacious with Corinth, even though they stabbed him in the back.

39:46.019 --> 39:49.983
As soon as he left, every time he left, they stabbed him in the back and he presses on.

39:50.023 --> 39:50.203
Why?

39:50.364 --> 39:52.446
Because I received a calling from the Lord.

39:53.667 --> 39:54.608
It came from Jesus.

39:54.669 --> 39:55.690
Jesus called me to this.

39:56.130 --> 39:57.472
Jesus is Lord.

39:57.812 --> 39:59.474
I trust him implicitly.

40:02.402 --> 40:07.829
Why would you go to Jerusalem knowing verse 23 that in every city imprisonment and afflictions await you?

40:07.909 --> 40:13.156
Because Jesus called me, period, and he's Lord, and he's worth trusting.

40:13.497 --> 40:15.980
I didn't expect it to be easy, and he's worth it.

40:17.823 --> 40:18.544
That's ministry.

40:19.084 --> 40:19.966
Think about your calling.

40:22.128 --> 40:27.756
Think about your specific place in life, season of life, your calling before God, because you have one.

40:27.796 --> 40:29.298
You have a ministry that God

40:29.410 --> 40:34.256
has called you to, that these kinds of things should be taking shape in that setting.

40:34.696 --> 40:35.577
Think about your calling.

40:37.680 --> 40:39.121
Where are you tempted to quit?

40:40.463 --> 40:41.925
Just take a moment and think about that.

40:41.945 --> 40:45.589
Where are you tempted to throw in the towel and say, okay, this is going nowhere.

40:45.629 --> 40:47.231
This is accomplishing nothing.

40:47.391 --> 40:51.736
I'm angry, I'm impatient, there's no fruit there, I'm just gonna stop.

40:51.996 --> 40:52.457
Think about it.

40:55.720 --> 40:57.042
Well, how do you respond to that?

40:58.370 --> 41:00.293
Now those are the realities of ministry.

41:00.333 --> 41:02.996
Not all the churches that Paul planted were doing great.

41:03.016 --> 41:04.057
I mean, read the letters.

