41:27.266 --> 41:29.070
Struggling, did we labor in vain?

41:29.110 --> 41:30.353
He asked those kinds of questions.

41:30.373 --> 41:31.535
Are we laboring in vain?

41:31.575 --> 41:34.301
It's a reality.

41:34.341 --> 41:37.608
The frustrations of ministry and not seeing adequate fruit.

41:37.648 --> 41:39.011
Where are you tempted to quit?

41:39.251 --> 41:43.100
Friend, ask God to renew your strength.

41:45.104 --> 41:48.050
Ask God for times of refreshing.

41:48.514 --> 41:55.004
to strengthen your trembling knees and the arms that hang down as the prophet say, ask him for power.

41:55.024 --> 42:00.432
Pray your tears, pray your fears by all means, but don't take your hands off the plow.

42:00.733 --> 42:01.935
Don't turn back.

42:02.496 --> 42:05.460
Don't give up.

42:05.480 --> 42:09.206
Let God prove his faithfulness right where you are.

42:09.246 --> 42:11.970
Let him prove his faithfulness.

42:11.990 --> 42:12.611
What does that mean?

42:14.614 --> 42:16.978
So many things that the New Testament talks about.

42:17.122 --> 42:17.903
in this regard.

42:18.283 --> 42:19.865
It means keep your hands on the plow.

42:19.905 --> 42:21.026
It means keep sowing.

42:21.767 --> 42:25.612
If it means don't neglect Sabbath, don't forget the place of rest.

42:28.955 --> 42:38.366
It means fix your eyes on Christ, looking to Him, the author and the perfecter of their faith, the people you're trying to serve, the kids you're trying to serve, the church, the small group you're trying to serve.

42:38.586 --> 42:40.108
He is the author and perfecter of their faith.

42:40.128 --> 42:41.810
He's the author and perfecter of your faith.

42:42.818 --> 42:47.243
He's the one who's gonna complete the work that he's begun in your small group and complete the work that he's begun.

42:47.663 --> 42:50.987
And you remember, friend, remember the gospel when you fail.

42:52.428 --> 42:57.434
Lean into the glorious truth of that robe of righteousness that'll never come off.

42:57.454 --> 42:58.475
You'll never need another one.

42:58.495 --> 42:59.436
It'll never wear out.

42:59.736 --> 43:00.417
It's perfect.

43:00.477 --> 43:01.038
It's glorious.

43:01.098 --> 43:05.082
It stands you in the presence of a holy God once and for all.

43:06.263 --> 43:07.524
Lean into the good of the gospel.

43:07.585 --> 43:08.726
Remember it when you fail.

43:08.766 --> 43:12.690
Trust God's nearness and God's presence

43:12.834 --> 43:13.695
in your pain.

43:16.319 --> 43:22.728
There is a fellowship with Christ that is sweetest when we are at the end of ourselves.

43:23.649 --> 43:24.110
Isn't that true?

43:26.092 --> 43:26.693
Get that.

43:28.095 --> 43:33.102
Get that sweetness, leverage that place of hardship and pain.

43:34.784 --> 43:41.874
Remember the truths of how the Savior did His work in the world, how He worked with people, shared good news with

43:41.954 --> 44:01.073
sinners, shared good news with the self-righteous, and remember the shape and the contours of Christ-centered ministry where dying is gained, where weakness is strength, where risk is right, where Christ is worth it, where Christ is coming.

44:01.473 --> 44:10.482
And with all those truths, talk to way deep in your heart, run your race, finish your

44:10.914 --> 44:16.722
of course, fulfill your ministry for the glory of the one who gave you that calling.

